ZH:我在考试前的准备上没有反省，所以考得很糟糕。
EN:I didn't reflect on my preparation before the exam, so I performed poorly.

ZH:她认识到自己犯了错误，开始反省自己的行为。
EN:She realized she made a mistake and began to reflect on her actions.

ZH:每天晚上，我会反省一天的工作和决策。
EN:Every night, I reflect on my work and decisions throughout the day.

ZH:经历了那次失败，他反省了自己的原因。
EN:After that failure, he reflected on his reasons.

ZH:他在失业期间反省了自己过去的职业选择。
EN:He reflected on his past career choices during his unemployment.

ZH:她反省了自己对待他人的态度，并决定改变。
EN:She reflected on her attitude towards others and decided to make a change.

ZH:我反省了自己的观点，并更加开放地听取别人的意见。
EN:I reflected on my viewpoints and became more open to listening to others' opinions.

ZH:我希望我能及时反省自己的错误，并学会改正。
EN:I hope I can reflect on my mistakes in time and learn to correct them.

ZH:反省可以帮助我们认识到自己的不足之处。
EN:Reflection can help us realize our shortcomings.

ZH:反省是个人成长的关键步骤之一。
EN:Reflection is one of the key steps in personal growth.

ZH:反省不仅仅关乎过去，它还能帮助我们更好地规划未来。
EN:Reflection is not just about the past, it also helps us better plan for the future.

ZH:反省让我明白了自己应该更加珍惜身边的人。
EN:Reflection made me realize that I should cherish the people around me more.

ZH:我会定期反省和审视自己的生活习惯。
EN:I will reflect on and examine my lifestyle habits regularly.

ZH:反省帮助我了解到自己的弱点，以便有针对性地改进。
EN:Reflection helps me understand my weaknesses so that I can improve with specificity.

ZH:每个人都需要有时间反省自己的生活和目标。
EN:Everyone needs time to reflect on their life and goals.

ZH:他在沉默中反省，找到了解决问题的办法。
EN:He reflected in silence and found a solution to the problem.

ZH:反省是成为更好的自己的关键步骤之一。
EN:Reflection is one of the key steps to becoming a better version of oneself.

ZH:她坚信通过反省可以不断进步。
EN:She firmly believes that progress can be made through reflection.

ZH:反省教会了我如何破除固有的偏见。
EN:Reflection taught me how to break free from inherent biases.

ZH:我们应该反省自己的言行是否符合道德标准。
EN:We should reflect on whether our words and actions conform to moral standards.
